snippet.textDisplay:
With utmost respect, There are a lot of pronunciation errors in the song. Probably because this kalam was written in Braj/Bhojpuri in ancient India. 
Its Nizamuddin not Nijamudin
Its Paschim not pachim
its piya not pira ka
its Dakshin not dakkhan (This one's still fine)
Its Ujiyaro not ujiraro
Qawwals should pronounce well
No offense.. I loved the song.. But hindi pronunciation is different from Urdu pronunciation

snippet.textDisplay:
Indeed a transcendental performance by the maestro vocalists. 
Less patent but just as significant, the laudable yet dominant percussionist (tabla player). 
What a mastery of laya and layakari! and the swift switches between khula baaj and bandh baaj- ingenious
Cheers to Coke Studio for bringing such authentic and pristine music to the wider audience.
Warm greetings from Britain!
